<!-- CTA Section -->
<section class="cta-section py-5">
    <div class="container text-center">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-lg-8">
                <h2 class="mb-4">מוכנים לח# thoughts
I need to create a Hebrew restaurant website for "Sumo" Asian kitchen inspired by Minna Tomei's design. Looking at the Minna Tomei website, I can see it has:
- Beautiful RTL Hebrew layout
- Multiple Asian cuisine sections (India, Japan, Thailand, Korea, Vietnam)
- Clean, modern design with elegant typography
- Restaurant locations and booking functionality
- Photo galleries and menu displays
- Blue/red color scheme as requested

For Sumo, I'll create a Flask application with:
- RTL Hebrew layout using Bootstrap RTL
- Blue and red branding colors
- Menu sections for different Asian cuisines
- Contact forms for reservations
- Photo gallery using the provided stock photos
- Responsive design
- Proper Hebrew typography

I'll structure it as a single-page application with multiple sections, similar to Minna Tomei's approach.

# useful_guidelines_from_blueprints
- Listen on port 5000 when starting a server
- Use Flask with proper secret key configuration
- Set secret_key as: app.secret_key = os.environ.get("SESSION_SECRET")
- Use Flask-Mail for contact forms and Flask-WTF for form handling
- Enable debug mode and use logging for debugging
- Create beautiful, functional, and production-ready design
- Avoid complex initialization in main.py

# directory_structure
```json
[
    {"path": "app.py", "status": "new"},
    {"path": "main.py", "status": "new"},
    {"path": "routes.py", "status": "new"},
    {"path": "forms.py", "status": "new"},
    {"path": "templates/base.html", "status": "new"},
    {"path": "templates/index.html", "status": "new"},
    {"path": "static/css/style.css", "status": "new"},
    {"path": "static/js/main.js", "status": "new"}
]
